    "actions": [
      {
        "startDie": 1,
        "endDie": 2,
        "name": "Grasping Claw (Physical)",
        "description": "<div><p>The Rotwalker extends a decaying arm, attempting to grasp a target with its skeletal hand, dealing D4 Necrotic damage on a hit. Additionally, the target must succeed on a Dodge check or be Restrained, as the Rotwalker's grip tightens.</p></div>"
      },
      {
        "startDie": 3,
        "endDie": 4,
        "name": "Festering Aura",
        "description": "<div><p>The Rotwalker emits a foul aura of decay around itself. Creatures within the aura must succeed on an Endurance check or take 2 Necrotic damage at the start of each of their turns. The aura lasts for 2 rounds or until the Rotwalker is destroyed. The duration is cumulative if Festering Cloud is rolled again.</p></div>"
      },
      {
        "startDie": 5,
        "endDie": 6,
        "name": "Deathly Embrace",
        "description": "<div><p>The Rotwalker lunges at a target, attempting to pull them into a ghastly embrace. The target must succeed on an Athletics check or be Restrained. While grappled, the target takes ongoing 1 Necrotic damage at the start of each of their turns until they break free or the Rotwalker is destroyed. The Rotwalker doesn't act against a character while they are affected by this Action; it will either change target or simply wait for the character to die or free themselves.</p></div>"
      }
    ],
    "description": "<div><p>A Rotwalkerâ€™s wretched form is that of a once-human creature, now consumed by the relentless march of decomposition. Its pallid, leathery skin hangs loosely from its skeletal frame, exposing festering wounds and bones in a gruesome display of mortality's defeat. The Rotwalker's eyes, hollow and devoid of life, glow with an unholy, malevolent light, seeking out the living with a ravenous hunger. The stench of death and decay precedes its arrival, warning the unfortunate of its relentless pursuit.</p></div>",
